messages.content:
Here's draft language for liability cap carve-outs:

**"Notwithstanding the limitation of liability set forth above, the liability cap shall not apply to:**

**(a) Data Security Breaches:** Any actual damages, costs, expenses, fines, penalties, or other liabilities arising from or related to (i) any unauthorized access to, disclosure of, or loss of Customer Data or Personal Information caused by Vendor's breach of its security obligations, (ii) Vendor's failure to comply with applicable data protection laws including but not limited to GDPR, CCPA, or HIPAA, or (iii) any cyber security incident resulting from Vendor's failure to maintain industry-standard security measures;

**(b) Intellectual Property Infringement:** Any damages, costs, expenses, settlements, or judgments arising from claims that Vendor's services or technology infringe, misappropriate, or violate any third party's intellectual property rights;

**(c) Confidentiality Violations:** Any damages resulting from Vendor's unauthorized use or disclosure of Customer's Confidential Information;

**(d) Gross Negligence and Willful Misconduct:** Any damages arising from Vendor's gross negligence, willful misconduct, or intentional breach of this Agreement;

**(e) Indemnification Obligations:** All costs and expenses that Vendor is obligated to indemnify Customer for under this Agreement."**

This language ensures unlimited liability for your highest-risk scenarios while maintaining the cap for other operational issues.
